    {
      "@id": "collection:conjugation-tags",
      "@type": "sbol:Collection",
      "dcterms:description": "Tags that form a covalent or enzyme-mediated link to a partner, for irreversible bioconjugation, site-specific labelling, or modular protein assembly. The collection covers the spontaneous isopeptide 'superglue' pairs SpyTag/SpyCatcher (and the faster SpyTag002/003) and the orthogonal SnoopTag/SnoopCatcher; the enzymatic systems AviTag (site-specifically biotinylated by the biotin ligase BirA) and the sortase-A LPETG motif (transpeptidation onto an N-terminal oligoglycine); and the self-labeling protein tag SNAP-tag, which covalently captures O6-benzylguanine\u2013linked probes. These parts are deployed as cognate pairs (tag + catcher/enzyme/substrate).",
      "dcterms:title": "Conjugation & self-labeling systems",
      "sbol:displayId": "conjugation-tags",
      "sbol:hasNamespace": {
        "@id": "https://w3id.org/seqmake/parts/"
      },
