      "cat:slug": "HRV3C_site",
      "dcterms:description": "Human rhinovirus 3C protease recognition and cleavage site (LEVLFQGP; Leu-Glu-Val-Leu-Phe-Gln-Gly-Pro). The 3C cysteine protease cleaves the peptide bond between Q (P1) and G (P1'), i.e. LEVLFQ|GP, leaving a Gly-Pro N-terminal scar on the downstream protein. The site derives from the natural HRV polyprotein processing sequence at residues 1423-1430 of HRV3 (UniProt Q82081). It is the recognition sequence used in the PreScission protease reagent (a GST-HRV3C fusion). Source-verified to UniProt Q82081 (POLG_HRV3) at 100% identity over all 8 aa. No functional sub-features are present: this is a single atomic cleavage-site element.",
      "dcterms:references": [
