      "cat:slug": "HaloTag",
      "cat:sourceAccession": "NCBI:ADN27525.1",
      "dcterms:description": "HaloTag7 self-labeling protein tag, 297 aa. Engineered monomeric haloalkane dehalogenase derived from Rhodococcus rhodochrous DhaA, carrying mutations that (i) abolish the second hydrolytic step so the enzyme-substrate covalent intermediate is trapped, and (ii) improve folding, solubility, and binding kinetics. Forms a rapid, essentially irreversible covalent ester bond with synthetic chloroalkane ligands. No coordinate-verified internal sub-features were retained; the catalytic residues (nucleophilic Asp at the alpha/beta-hydrolase nucleophile elbow, motif IGMGKSDK; the engineered His->Phe that prevents hydrolytic release) are mechanistic and are captured as functional_claims rather than as residue-level features.",
      "dcterms:references": [
        {
          "@id": "https://identifiers.org/pubmed:18533659"
        },
        {
          "@id": "https://identifiers.org/pubmed:19464373"
        },
