      "cat:sourceAccession": "UniProt:P0AFF6",
      "dcterms:description": "E. coli K-12 NusA (N-utilization substance protein A), 495 aa, UniProt P0AFF6. Essential transcription elongation factor that enhances transcriptional pausing and intrinsic termination; displaced from RNAP by sigma at initiation. Multi-domain architecture: NTD (aa 1\u2013137, interacts with RNAP beta-flap tip helix), S1 RNA-binding domain, KH RNA-binding domain, AR1 (interacts with bacteriophage lambda N antiterminator), AR2 (autoinhibitory). Also widely deployed as an N-terminal solubility-enhancing fusion tag in recombinant protein expression.",
