        }
      ],
      "cat:slug": "SNAP_tag",
      "dcterms:description": "SNAP-tag self-labeling protein domain (179 aa), engineered by directed evolution from human O6-alkylguanine-DNA alkyltransferase (hAGT/MGMT, P16455). Covalently and irreversibly transfers the benzyl group of O6-benzylguanine (BG) substrates to its active-site cysteine (the I-P-C-H-R active-site motif; reactive Cys at residue 144 in this stored numbering, equivalent to canonical hAGT Cys145), thereby self-labeling the fusion protein with whatever chemical probe is appended to the BG. The 178-aa core (residues 2-179) is a 100% exact match to UniProt E5BBQ0 (182 aa, derived from PDB 3KZY) and PDB 3KZY chain A. The functional M-start ORF (179 aa) is used here; the deposited crystallography construct (E5BBQ0/3KZY, 182 aa) instead carries a GPGS cloning prefix in place of the initiator Met. Closest canonical reference: UniProt E5BBQ0 (unreviewed TrEMBL).",
      "dcterms:references": [
        {
          "@id": "https://identifiers.org/pubmed:12469133"
        },
        {
          "@id": "https://identifiers.org/pubmed:12725859"
