    {
      "@id": "part:SNAP_tag_claim_origin",
      "@type": "cat:FunctionalClaim",
      "cat:analysisStatus": "pending",
      "cat:claimType": "origin",
      "cat:claimValue": "{\"canonical_reference_record\": \"UniProt E5BBQ0 (derived from PDB 3KZY)\", \"engineering\": \"directed evolution / phage-display selection of hAGT mutant libraries\", \"parent_protein\": \"human O6-alkylguanine-DNA alkyltransferase (hAGT / AGT / MGMT)\", \"selected_for\": \"efficient covalent reaction with O6-benzylguanine substrates\"}",
      "cat:confidence": "high",
      "cat:crossChecked": false,
      "cat:sourceQuote": "We report here the generation of mutants of the human O(6)-alkylguanine-DNA alkyltransferase (hAGT) for the efficient in vivo labeling of fusion proteins with synthetic reporter molecules. Libraries of hAGT were displayed on phage, and mutants capable of efficiently reacting with the inhibitor O(6)-benzylguanine were selected",
