          "@id": "part:SpyCatcher_claim_application"
        }
      ],
      "cat:slug": "SpyCatcher",
      "dcterms:description": "116-aa protein partner of the SpyTag/SpyCatcher covalent-conjugation system, engineered by splitting the CnaB2 immunoglobulin-like collagen-adhesion domain of Streptococcus pyogenes fibronectin-binding protein FbaB into a protein fragment (SpyCatcher, contains the reactive Lys31) and a 13-aa peptide (SpyTag, contains the reactive Asp). On mixing with SpyTag, the side-chain amine of SpyCatcher Lys31 spontaneously and irreversibly forms an intermolecular isopeptide (amide) bond to SpyTag Asp7, catalysed by SpyCatcher Glu77; the linkage resists boiling in SDS and forces up to ~1 nN. As stored the domain begins with a vector-derived Gly-Ala-Met (residues 24-139 of AFD50637.1, the standard post-TEV-cleavage product) and is fusable at a protein N- or C-terminus. Structural and biochemical work shows the N-terminal ~23 and C-terminal ~9 residues are dispensable, defining a minimized 84-aa core (original residues 21-104).",
      "dcterms:references": [
        {
          "@id": "https://identifiers.org/pubmed:22366317"
        },
        {
          "@id": "https://identifiers.org/pubmed:24161952"
        },
        {
