      "@id": "part:SpyCatcher_claim_conditions",
      "@type": "cat:FunctionalClaim",
      "cat:analysisStatus": "pending",
      "cat:claimType": "conditions",
      "cat:claimValue": "{\"high_solubility\": \"complex concentrated to >110 mg/ml\", \"robust_conditions\": \"diverse pH, temperature, and buffer\", \"stability\": \"covalent complex not reversed by boiling in SDS or competing peptide; bond breaks only above ~1 nN force\"}",
      "cat:confidence": "medium",
      "cat:crossChecked": false,
      "cat:sourceQuote": "Reaction occurred in high yield simply upon mixing and amidst diverse conditions of pH, temperature, and buffer ... Peptide binding was not reversed by boiling or competing peptide. Single-molecule dynamic force spectroscopy showed that SpyTag did not separate from SpyCatcher until the force exceeded 1 nN, where covalent bonds snap.",
      "cat:sourceQuoteFrom": "primary",
      "cat:sourceSection": "Abstract",
