      "cat:claimValue": "{\"design\": \"split of CnaB2 into a protein fragment (SpyCatcher, Lys31) and a peptide (SpyTag, Asp) plus rational engineering\", \"organism\": \"Streptococcus pyogenes\", \"parent_domain\": \"CnaB2 (immunoglobulin-like collagen adhesion domain; PDB 2X5P)\", \"parent_protein\": \"fibronectin-binding protein FbaB\", \"sequence_record\": \"AFD50637.1 / JQ478411.1, residues 24-139 (post-TEV product, N-terminal Gly-Ala-Met)\"}",
      "cat:confidence": "high",
      "cat:crossChecked": false,
      "cat:sourceQuote": "fibronectin-binding protein FbaB contains a domain with a spontaneous isopeptide bond between Lys and Asp. By splitting this domain and rational engineering of the fragments, we obtained a peptide (SpyTag) which formed an amide bond to its protein partner (SpyCatcher)",
      "cat:sourceQuoteFrom": "primary",
      "cat:sourceSection": "Abstract",
      "dcterms:references": {
        "@id": "https://identifiers.org/pubmed:22366317"
