      "cat:analysisStatus": "pending",
      "cat:claimType": "sequence_feature",
      "cat:claimValue": "{\"c_terminal_dispensable\": \"last ~9 residues (backbone traceable only to residue 103; C-terminal 10 disordered)\", \"effect_of_minimization\": \"comparable reaction efficiency to full-length SpyCatcher\", \"minimal_core\": \"residues 21-104 of original SpyCatcher\", \"minimal_length_aa\": 84, \"n_terminal_dispensable\": \"first ~23 residues (disordered in crystal; deletable as SpyCatcherDeltaN1/N2/N3)\"}",
      "cat:confidence": "high",
      "cat:crossChecked": false,
      "cat:sourceQuote": "our structural and biochemical data indicate that a minimal SpyTag/SpyCatcher system consists of residues 21\u2013104 of the original SpyCatcher. The minimization of SpyCatcher from 116 amino acids to a core 84 amino acid construct should enhance its applicability as a fusion tag",
      "cat:sourceQuoteFrom": "primary",
      "cat:sourceSection": "The N-terminal and C-terminal segments of SpyCatcher are not required for efficient reaction with SpyTag",
      "dcterms:references": {
