      "cat:claimType": "sequence_variant",
      "cat:claimValue": "{\"original_rate_M-1_s-1\": 1400, \"variants\": [{\"fold_over_original\": \"~12-14\", \"name\": \"SpyCatcher002\", \"note\": \"phage-display-evolved pair with SpyTag002\", \"rate_constant_M-1_s-1\": 20000}, {\"fold_over_original\": \"~400\", \"mutations\": \"A89P, T91E, Q97D, N103D, K108E (relative to SpyCatcher002 lineage)\", \"name\": \"SpyCatcher003\", \"note\": \"approaches the diffusion limit; back-compatible with earlier SpyTag/SpyCatcher generations\", \"partner\": \"SpyTag003 (RG prefix + T112H)\", \"rate_constant_M-1_s-1\": 550000}, {\"name\": \"SpyCatcher E77A\", \"note\": \"single-residue catalytic knockout; abolishes isopeptide-bond formation (specificity / negative control)\"}]}",
      "cat:confidence": "high",
      "cat:crossChecked": false,
      "cat:sourceQuote": "we made 4 mutations (T91E, Q97D, N103D, and K108E) from SpyCatcher002 ... to give the final SpyCatcher003 ... The second-order rate constant for SpyTag003/SpyCatcher003 was 5.5 \u00b1 0.6 \u00d7 10[5] M[-1]s[-1] ... \u223c400-fold faster than the 1.4 \u00d7 10[3] M[-1]s[-1] previously shown for SpyTag/SpyCatcher",
      "cat:sourceQuoteFrom": "primary",
      "cat:sourceSection": "Results",
