      "cat:slug": "SpyTag002",
      "dcterms:description": "Second-generation 14-aa peptide tag (VPTIVMVDAYKRYK) derived from the CnaB2 immunoglobulin-like domain of Streptococcus pyogenes fibronectin-binding protein FbaB, evolved from the original SpyTag (AHIVMVDAYKPTK) by phage-display selection plus rational design. SpyTag002 differs from SpyTag at 4/13 shared residues and carries one extra N-terminal residue. On mixing with its protein partner SpyCatcher002 it forms a spontaneous, irreversible intermolecular isopeptide (amide) bond (reactive Asp; partner Lys; catalysed by SpyCatcher Glu77); single Asp->Ala (DA) mutation abolishes the reaction. Fusable at the N-terminus or C-terminus. Backwards-compatible with the parental SpyCatcher.",
      "dcterms:references": [
        {
          "@id": "https://identifiers.org/pubmed:29024296"
        },
        {
          "@id": "https://identifiers.org/pubmed:22366317"
        },
        {
          "@id": "https://identifiers.org/pubmed:30988307"
        },
        {
          "@id": "https://identifiers.org/pubmed:31822621"
        }
      ],
