      "cat:slug": "SpyTag003",
      "dcterms:description": "16-aa third-generation Spy peptide tag (RGVPHIVMVDAYKRYK). Engineered from SpyTag002 by appending an N-terminal Arg-Gly (RG) dipeptide and introducing the T112H mutation (CnaB2 numbering), descended from the CnaB2 domain of Streptococcus pyogenes FbaB. On mixing with its 116-aa partner SpyCatcher003 it forms a spontaneous, irreversible intermolecular isopeptide (amide) bond between its reactive Asp (CnaB2 Asp117) and Lys31 of SpyCatcher003, catalysed by SpyCatcher Glu77 - reaction approaches the diffusion limit. Fusable at N-terminus, C-terminus or internally. Contains no Cys.",
      "dcterms:references": [
        {
          "@id": "https://identifiers.org/pubmed:31822621"
        },
        {
          "@id": "https://identifiers.org/pubmed:22366317"
        },
