    {
      "@id": "part:SpyTag003_claim_conditions",
      "@type": "cat:FunctionalClaim",
      "cat:analysisStatus": "pending",
      "cat:claimType": "conditions",
      "cat:claimValue": "{\"compartments\": [\"extracellular / cell surface\", \"cytoplasm\"], \"low_concentration_performance\": \"half-time <5 min with both partners ~10 nM\", \"note\": \"earlier Spy generations show broad tolerance of pH, temperature and buffer and versatile fusion sites; the 003 pair inherits this robustness\", \"reference_buffer\": \"succinate-phosphate-glycine or PBS, pH 7.0-7.4, 25 C\"}",
      "cat:confidence": "high",
      "cat:crossChecked": false,
      "cat:sourceQuote": "even with each partner at a thousand-fold lower concentration, the reaction half-time is less than 5 min. Therefore, this covalent reactivity can be harnessed for the study of proteins over a range of cellular concentrations... Previous iterations have shown broad tolerance of reaction conditions and versatility in the sites of fusion.",
      "cat:sourceQuoteFrom": "primary",
      "cat:sourceSection": "Discussion",
      "dcterms:references": {
