      "cat:slug": "Ulp1",
      "cat:sourceAccession": "UniProt:Q02724",
      "dcterms:description": "Catalytic (UD/Ulp) domain of Saccharomyces cerevisiae Ulp1, residues 403-621 of the 621-aa UniProt Q02724 (ULP1_YEAST). SUMO/Smt3-specific cysteine protease (clan CE, SENP/Ulp family) that cleaves after the SUMO C-terminal Gly-Gly to release a passenger with a native (scarless) N-terminus. This minimal catalytic fragment is the canonical 403-621 crystallography/expression construct (PDB 1EUV) and is sufficient for the essential SUMO-deconjugation function in vivo.",
