      "cat:slug": "lambda_attB",
      "dcterms:description": "Lambda bacterial attachment site attB (B-O-B\u2032), the chromosomal target recombined with phage attP (lambda_attP) by lambda tyrosine integrase + IHF (Xis/Fis for excision). 21 bp minimal attB from NC_000913.3 (att\u03bb, between gal and bio); 15 bp common core O = GCTTTTTTATACTAA, with the 7 bp crossover overlap TTTATAC at which Int makes the staggered cut. Source-verified 100%. Cognate phage site: lambda_attP.",
