      "cat:slug": "phi80_attP",
      "dcterms:description": "Bacteriophage phi80 phage attachment site (attP), 480 bp. Recombination substrate for the phi80 tyrosine integrase (Int) acting with E. coli integration host factor (IHF); recombines with the chromosomal attB site in the E. coli thrW/yciI region to integrate the phi80 prophage (and, in the CRIM system, an attP-bearing plasmid). The 17 bp common core lies near the centre; the flanking P (positions ~279-480) and P' (positions ~0-262) arms carry the Int arm-type and IHF binding sites. Source AY048738.1 is the CRIM integration plasmid pAH162, which carries the phage attP.",
