    {
      "@id": "part:phi80_attP_claim_mechanism",
      "@type": "cat:FunctionalClaim",
      "cat:analysisStatus": "pending",
      "cat:claimType": "mechanism",
      "cat:claimValue": "{\"host_factor\": \"E. coli IHF\", \"mechanism\": \"phi80 attP is the phage attachment site recombined by the phi80 tyrosine integrase (Int) together with the host integration host factor (IHF). Int and IHF assemble on the attP arms (Int arm-type sites and a single IHF site in the P arm, analogous to lambda H2) to bring the 17 bp common core into the recombinogenic intasome; site-specific strand exchange across the core integrates phi80 (or an attP-bearing plasmid) into the cognate chromosomal attB site.\", \"recombinase\": \"phi80 integrase (Int), tyrosine recombinase family\"}",
      "cat:confidence": "medium",
      "cat:crossChecked": false,
      "cat:sourceQuote": "The phi80 and P22 attachment sites: primary structure and interaction with Escherichia coli integration host factor \u2014 phi80 attP has a 17 bp common core and a single IHF site in the P arm analogous to lambda H2.",
