          "@id": "part:phiC31_attP_claim_minimal_site"
        },
        {
          "@id": "part:phiC31_attP_claim_host_range"
        }
      ],
      "cat:slug": "phiC31_attP",
      "dcterms:description": "Phage attachment site (attP) of Streptomyces temperate phage phiC31, the DNA target recognized by the phiC31 large serine integrase. 100 bp spanning the attP crossover region; exact reverse complement of X57036.1 positions 1590-1689. The phiC31 integrase recombines this attP with a chromosomal attB to integrate DNA irreversibly and unidirectionally, with no required host accessory factors. Widely used as a chromosomal landing pad in heterologous hosts including mammalian cells. The functional center comprises two 9 bp imperfect inverted-repeat integrase half-sites flanking a spacer that carries the central TT crossover dinucleotide.",
      "dcterms:references": [
        {
          "@id": "https://identifiers.org/pubmed:1656389"
        },
        {
          "@id": "https://identifiers.org/pubmed:9576912"
        },
