      "cat:slug": "rrnBT1T2",
      "dcterms:description": "rrnB T1+T2 tandem double terminator: the complete T1-T2 intrinsic (Rho-independent) transcription terminator cluster located downstream of the 5S rRNA gene in the E. coli rrnB ribosomal RNA operon. 217 bp taken at 100% identity from the canonical rrnB operon sequence J01695 (positions 6362\u20136578, 1-based; Brosius et al. 1981). bp 1\u2013169 are the T1 terminator (catalog part rrnBT1); bp 170\u2013217 are the 3' portion of the T2 terminator region (overlapping the 3' end of catalog part rrnBT2). The two terminators function as a tandem unit that strongly and bidirectionally insulates downstream sequence from upstream transcription; both terminate host (E. coli sigma-70) RNA polymerase. Composite of catalog atoms rrnBT1 + rrnBT2; sourced fresh from J01695, not assembled by concatenation.",
