      ],
      "cat:slug": "thrombin_site",
      "dcterms:description": "Engineered 6-aa thrombin (factor IIa) recognition/cleavage site Leu-Val-Pro-Arg-Gly-Ser. Thrombin hydrolyses the peptide bond after the Arg (LVPR | GS), releasing the downstream protein with an N-terminal Gly-Ser scar. Derived from the natural human factor VIII thrombin site LVPRGF by a Phe->Ser substitution that creates a BamHI (GGATCC) cloning site; the canonical site of the pGEX-2T GST-fusion expression system. Source-verified to U13850.1 misc_feature 918..935 at 100% identity over all 6 residues.",
      "dcterms:references": [
        {
          "@id": "https://identifiers.org/pubmed:3047011"
        },
        {
          "@id": "https://identifiers.org/pubmed:22384068"
